==============================================================================
HUG TRACKER - FEATURE SUMMARY
==============================================================================

==============================================================================
ūüß† PURPOSE
==============================================================================
This interaction module lets one current attendee send a hug to another attendee
and updates both the giver‚Äôs and receiver‚Äôs long-term counters.

Self-hugs are intentionally rejected with a separate response. Successful hugs use
a randomized message and include the receiver‚Äôs newly updated total.

==============================================================================
ūüĒĄ SYSTEM FLOW
==============================================================================
STEP 1: COMMAND TARGETING
--------------------------------
- Reads user and removes !hug from rawInput to identify the target.
- Normalizes both usernames for validation and storage.

STEP 2: ATTENDANCE CHECK
--------------------------------
- Requires the invoker to exist in SeenUsers.
- Requires a separate target to exist in SeenUsers as well.

STEP 3: SELF-HUG HANDLING
--------------------------------
- Uses selfHugError when the target is blank or matches the invoker.
- Does not change counters for a rejected self-hug.

STEP 4: COUNTER UPDATE
--------------------------------
- Increments <invoker>_given and <target>_received inside HugStats.
- Saves the updated dictionary.

STEP 5: RANDOM CHAT MESSAGE
--------------------------------
- Selects a hug phrase, inserts both names and the receiver total, then posts it.

==============================================================================
ūüď¶ VARIABLE REFERENCE
==============================================================================
HugStats
--------------------------------
Dictionary storing every giver and receiver counter.

SeenUsers
--------------------------------
Current attendance dictionary required for command eligibility.

hugPhrases
--------------------------------
Randomized messages used for successful hugs.

selfHugError
--------------------------------
Fixed response used when a viewer targets themselves or supplies no target.

<username>_given / <username>_received
--------------------------------
Persistent keys updated after each successful hug.

==============================================================================
ūüé® USER CUSTOMIZATION
==============================================================================
COMMAND PARSING
--------------------------------
